          "body": "The chapter ends with a verse that functions as the gospel's final ultimatum: 'I do not nullify the grace of God, for if righteousness comes through the Law, then Christ died needlessly.' The Greek *dorean* — translated 'needlessly' — literally means 'gratuitously, for nothing.' Paul reduces the Judaizing position to absurdity. If any system of Law-keeping could produce righteousness before God, the cross of Christ was an unnecessary tragedy. But the cross *did* happen — therefore the Law cannot justify. The conclusion is binary and inescapable. To add anything to the cross as a basis for righteousness is to declare the cross insufficient — which is to declare it pointless. Every chapter that follows in Galatians (3-6) is built on this single foundation."
